text: Daphnella phyxelis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae.Barnard, K. H. "The work of the ss Pieter Faure in Natal waters, with special reference to the Crustacea and Mollusca; with descriptions of new species of Mollusca from Natal." Annals of the Natal Museum 16.1 (1964): 9-29. ==Description== The length of this broken shell may have been 12 mm long. The holotype consists of the protoconch and two subsequent whorls. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Natal, South Africa. ==References== ==External links== * phyxelis Category:Gastropods described in 1964
title: Daphnella phyxelis
